 285:Utilities/sequencer/stm32_seq.c ****         /*
 286:Utilities/sequencer/stm32_seq.c ****          * Due to the concept of TaskPrio[counter].round_robin and TaskClearList, it could be that 
 287:Utilities/sequencer/stm32_seq.c ****          * (when using UTIL_SEQ_WaitEvt()), that there is a situation where at the same time, a bit
 288:Utilities/sequencer/stm32_seq.c ****          * and reset in TaskClearList and another bit is set in TaskClearList and reset in TaskPrio
